# Conversation Validation™ (Spec 119) — FROZEN

**Architecture:** [FREEZE](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_ARCHITECTURE_FREEZE.md) · **Framework:** [Spec 119](../docs/SPARK_CONVERSATION_TESTS_FRAMEWORK.md)

**Scorecard:** `docs/conversation-tests/SCORECARD_TEMPLATE.md` · **Tests:** `ct-01.md` … `ct-11.md`

## Phase: validate — not design

Do NOT redesign Spark · UI · workflows · features. **Improve conversations. Test again.**

## Mandate

**Break the Conversation Engine.** Never declare "Passed."

## Eight mandatory QA gates (every test)

1. **Conversation Quality** — 10 categories, 1–10
2. **Hospitality™** (111) — 5 pass/fail
3. **Cognitive Load** — 🟢🟡🔴
4. **Iceberg** (118) — submerged work + permission boundary
5. **Relief Test™** — 🟢 increased · 🟡 no change · 🔴 decreased
6. **Future Me Test™** — tomorrow easier?
7. **Spark Question™** — software vs Shari? → turn · why · rewrite
8. **Shari Over-the-Shoulder** — **mandatory** — warmth · pace · trust · ADHD friendliness

## On failure

Exact turn · why · rewrite that response only · nearest Gold Standard (116)

## Final question

Companion for 20 minutes — or operating an application?

